  "name": "AM Receiver — 1610 kHz (KLIX)",
  "description": "Phase 1 breadboard AM receiver. Tank circuit tunes to 1610 kHz. 1N4148 envelope detector. LM386 audio output stage to crystal earpiece. Single 18650 Li-ion supply.",
  "notes": "L1+C1+C_trim = tank circuit. Resonant freq: f = 1/(2π√(LC)). 220µH + 100pF + 50pF trimmer ≈ 1.58–1.67 MHz range covers 1610 kHz. Trim C to exactly 1610 kHz by ear or with scope. D1 = envelope detector. C2 = post-detector AF filter. C3 = LM386 input coupling. C4 = output filter. RV1 = volume. BT1 = 18650 @ 3.7V.",
